  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nOther (please describe)\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\ncast 0.2.0 (5490c4a 2022-04-25T13:44:02.750924985+00:00)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\ncargo run --bin cast -- run 0xcd314668aaa9bbfebaf1a0bd2b6553d01dd58899c508d4729fa7311dc5d33ad7 --debug\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nOnly happens on a debug build and **not release**.\r\nUsing `gas.spend().saturated_sub(...` would silence it, but I feel like it shouldn't overflow in the first place? \r\n\r\n```shell\r\nExecuting previous transactions from the block.\r\nThe application panicked (crashed).\r\nMessage:  attempt to subtract with overflow\r\nLocation: /home/user/foundry/evm/src/executor/inspector/debugger.rs:161\r\n\r\nBacktrace omitted. Run with RUST_BACKTRACE=1 environment variable to display it.\r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=full to include source snippets.\r\n```\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nlet total_gas_spent = gas.spend() - self.previous_gas_block + self.current_gas_block;\r\n```\r\n",
